archetypes.name: Limits to Success
archetypes.rationale: The model shows growth in Core Developers through promotion from New Contributors, but Developer Turnover creates a balancing constraint that limits this growth, though the explicit limiting factor isn't clearly defined.

variables.name: Workload Pressure
variables.description: Pressure on existing developers due to high workload
variables.rationale: To represent the constraint that causes turnover and limits growth

variables.name: Sustainable Capacity
variables.description: Maximum number of developers the system can sustainably support
variables.rationale: To represent the limiting factor that creates the balancing loop

connections.rationale: More developers reduce individual workload pressure

archetypes.name: Growth and Underinvestment
archetypes.rationale: The model shows knowledge transfer mechanisms (mentorship and documentation) that could represent capacity investment, but lacks clear connection between developer growth and investment in these capacity-building systems.

variables.name: Investment in Knowledge Systems
variables.description: Resources allocated to improving knowledge transfer systems
variables.rationale: To represent the investment decision that affects capacity

variables.name: Perceived Performance Gap
variables.description: Difference between desired and actual performance
variables.rationale: To drive investment decisions when performance declines

archetypes.name: Shifting the Burden
archetypes.rationale: The model shows both implicit (mentorship) and explicit (documentation) knowledge transfer, suggesting potential symptom vs fundamental solution dynamics, but lacks clear distinction between quick fixes and fundamental solutions.

variables.name: Fundamental Solution Investment
variables.rationale: To represent the fundamental solution side of the archetype

variables.name: Quick Fix Pressure
variables.rationale: To represent the symptom-relief side of the archetype

connections.rationale: High turnover creates pressure for quick fixes
Pressure drives investment in documentation as quick fix
Quick fix pressure reduces focus on fundamental solutions
